Delta State government, yesterday, reconstituted Delta State Traditional Rulers Council with the Orodje of Okpe Kingdom, Major General Felix Mujakperuo (rtd) as the new chairman, five days after the dissolution of Obi Emmanuel Efeizomor-led council. Mujakperuo was the first vice chairman of the dissolved Efeizomor-led council. The Secretary to the State Government, Patrick Ukah, signed the reconstituted letter, dated January 25. According to the letter, the Governor, Dr. Ifeanyi Okowa, approved the reconstituted council with the Pere of Akugbene-Mien Kingdom, Pere Stanley P. Luke, now the first vice chairman. The new council also has the Obi of Ubulu-Unor, Agbogidi, and Obi Henry A. Kikachukwu, as the 2nd vice-chairman. The council is usually a sixty-member body of traditional rulers from the three senatorial districts of the state.